##Introduction
On Day 1 of the NGS bootcamp, I learned the basic concepts of Next Generation Sequencing (NGS) and practiced Basic Linux commands in an Ubuntu (WSL) environment.

##Linux Commands Learned
- 'pwd' → Displays the current working directory
- 'ls' → Lists files and directories
- 'cd' → Changes directory
- 'mkdir' → Creates a new directory
- 'touch' → Creates a new file
- 'echo' → Writes text into a file
- 'cat' → Displays file content
- 'nano' → Opens a file in a text editor

##Practical Work
Created a folder named NGS
Created a subfolder data inside NGS
Created a text file using touch
Added content using echo
Viewed file content using cat
Edited file using nano

##Conclusion
This session helped me build a strong foundation in  Linux basics and file handling, which are essential for working with NGS data and bioinformatics tools.
